            <title>[CXF-7588] SAML audience restriction validation is enabled by default for REST services</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7588</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a regression due to the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7444&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7444&lt;/a&gt;. Previously, JAX-RS SAML services did not enable audience restriction validation by default. However, with the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7444&quot; title=&quot;Add the ability to configure custom SAML audience restriction values&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-7444&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-7444&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; validation was inadvertently enabled by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
